This paper proposes a faster alternative to Bi-LSTMs for NER, which is a task in computational linguistics and falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their training procedures, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of GPU hardware, which is a common tool in parallel computing and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
